cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or the RadSaFE-200 benchmark, please cite the accompanying paper."
title: "SaFE-Scale: safety-focused evaluation of scaling for clinical large language models"
abstract: >
  Code release accompanying \"Safety and accuracy follow different scaling
  laws in clinical large language models\". Reproduces the SaFE-Scale
  evaluation pipeline (Radiopaedia-based RAG context construction,
  multi-condition vLLM inference across 34 models, LLM-judge answer
  verification, and bootstrap statistical analysis of accuracy, safety
  rates, dangerous overconfidence, self-consistency, and ensemble failure
  modes) on the RadSaFE-200 benchmark.
